// toggle.su — flip a 0/1 GUI state as a real substrate-state RNN.
//
// The recurring state vector lives ON THE SUBSTRATE between clicks, in the
// non-halting-loop slot (planning/sutra-spec/non-halting-loop.md, Emma
// 2026-05-28). flip() takes no argument; each call loads the substrate
// slot, computes `make_real(1.0) - state` (vector subtraction; if state's
// real axis is 0 the result's is 1, and vice versa), writes the new state
// back via recur(...), and returns the new state vector. The host reads
// the result for display at the boundary (_display.read_real), not feedback.
// Measured 2026-06-11: flip() x4 with no host feedback = [1,0,1,0].
//
// Same shape as count.su's step() — both are substrate-state RNNs where
// the click is purely a trigger and the state never round-trips through
// a host scalar between calls. Closes CLAUDE.md "Subtler substrate
// breaches" #2 for this demo.
//
// @fv-claim: rnn test=demos/gui/test_gui_click.py
function vector flip() {
    recurring vector state = make_real(0.0);
    vector new_state = make_real(1.0) - state;
    recur(new_state);
    return(new_state);
}

function vector main() { return flip(); }
